page.title: 02Housing
page.content: In Gedney Hill there are quite a lot of council houses.There are some new houses and chalet bungalows etc.. Modern houses are made out of bricks. Some people live in caravans while their houses are being built.There are still quite a lot of people living in cottages that are part of a farm.Most old cottages face the South. Some old houses are being knocked down and new ones are being built in their place. In Gedney Hill there are a lot more houses than bungalows. Lots of people have gardens and vegetable plots.Some people have a lot of trees growing in their front gardens.People who have gardens have bigger ones than people in town. Some people in Gedney Hill have static caravans down near the beach at Heacham,Hunstanton and Skegness.
